post_text:
Estimados Padres/Tutores
La prioridad de CUSD es la salud, el bienestar social y emocional y el éxito académico de nuestros estudiantes. Debido a las preocupaciones actuales de seguridad y las necesidades de distanciamiento social continuo, no está claro cuándo nuestros estudiantes podrán regresar a los planteles escolares. Con el fin de permitirnos planificar en consecuencia, y para garantizar que el aprendizaje todavía se produzca durante el verano, ofreceremos la Escuela de Verano de Aprendizaje a Distancia. A continuación, se muestra un enlace a nuestra Solicitud de la Escuela de Verano de Aprendizaje a Distancia para nuestros estudiantes actuales de kínder a octavo grado. Por favor complete una solicitud por cada estudiante que vaya a participar.

https://bit.ly/cusdss2020

post_text:
Dear Parents/Guardians
CUSD’s priority is the health, social-emotional well-being, and academic success of our students. Due to the current safety concerns and needs for ongoing social distancing, it is uncertain when our students will be able to return to school campuses. In order to allow us to plan accordingly, and to ensure that learning still occurs during the summer, we will be offering Distance Learning Summer School. Below is a link to our Distance Learning Summer School Application for our current Kinder through eighth grade students. Please submit one application for each student participating.

https://bit.ly/cusdss2020

It gives us great pleasure to announce that our Migrant Debate Team, representing Willie Moreno Junior High and Enrique Camarena Junior High, won 1st place at the California Migrant State Finals Competition, representing the Imperial Valley, Region 6 in Ventura Beach and Ornard High School. Displays/exhibits on sea life and oceanography will be available for students and staff through this week, April 16-20, 2018 in the school's library.. Registration for Calexico kindergarten students will be on going beginning Monday, April 9, 2018. Registration hours will be from 1:00 p.m. to 3:30 p.m. at the school’s office or cafeteria. Parents must bring copies of child’s birth certificate, completed immunization card, and proofs of residency (mortgage or rental contract, rental receipt, and two current utility bills (electric, water or gas). A kindergartener must have their 5th birthday on or before September 1, 2018. [ 146 more words ]
